4.      
D1.3 – When Fire Isolated Stairways are Required
Performance Solution #5
It is proposed to permit the Eastern Basement stair to be an open stair that connects four (4) stories.
It is noted that stair pressurisation would not be required in an open stair.
A Performance Solution is to be formulated to comply with BCA Performance Requirements DP4.




You are kindly requested to accept an invitation from BOX cloud storage service that you will receive soon, this invitation will allow each one of you to access/edit a specific folder allocated for each discipline, please make sure to upload your drawings to your BOX folder link and always keep your folder updated, other consultants will access your folder to download the latest design that you provide. The folders being always updated is the responsibility of each related consultant.
 
In addition, please find attached the following documents FYI and kind review, this information are also included in the link:
 
    CC Building General Specifications list
    Developer & Builder required items list
    FF&E schedules. Will be filled by the client soon.
    Consultants list, it will allow you to contact any consultant that you need to coordinate with, please make sure to ask any consultant directly for information and cc myself, Rami, Joseph, Surini, Paul Sarkissian, and Paul Lugo, Façade and Waterproofing consultants will be engaged soon.
 
UL standard procedure after engaging the consultants is the following to avoid any abortive work:
 
    Ask EL/ME/HY/ST to provide their spatial requirements markups on the submitted Section 4.55 drawings that will be approved very soon, and the BCA consultant to provide the BCA assessment summary, the markups are hand sketches and we ask no progress in developing your layouts before we provide you with the CC GAPs.
    Update our architectural CC layouts.
    Provide the PCA with CC layouts and the list of changes in comparison with approved DA and ask for advice.
    Ask the consultants to progress in CC/CD packages based on the PCA advice and the CC Checklist after getting OK to progress from the client.
 
Few Important notes to be considered prior to moving forward with your spatial planning and design requirements:
 
    Consider and review ALL documents provided in the project link.
    DA conditions and CC checklist to be checked and all relevant consultants to ensure he/she adheres to the relevant section related to them.
    Review all documents provided by the builder such as NOR, Detailed Survey, Services locations, Boundary alignment Levels, Pressure Inquiry and L3 max. demand.
    Review the Structural Design “basic and preliminary mark-up”, this will allow you to coordinate your services efficiently.
 
To move forward with this project, we require you to provide us with your spatial planning requirements (Hand Sketches ONLY), please be mindful that NO CAD drawings to be executed until we get back to you with a written email confirming to proceed with this and after the layouts are locked.
 
May I request your hand sketches/mark-up and comments to be provided within the next “four” business days, no later than COB Monday 04/04/2022.
 
Thank you Team, looking forward to hearing back from you.
 
Should you have any inquiries, please do not hesitate to contact me.
 
Regards,
 
Wail NOURI
Associate Director – Principal Design Manager
B. (Architecture Engineering), H. Dip. (Architecture Science)
